comments: Mitchell (SAC) maintains his arms within the frame of his body and does not deliver illegal contact to Walker IV (LAL) during the pick.
Reaves (LAL) legally contests Huerter's (SAC) jump shot attempt.
Beverley (LAL) makes contact with Sabonis (SAC) that impedes his ability to pursue the rebound.
Beverley (LAL) and Fox (SAC) engage and disengage with one another and marginal contact occurs as the screen is set.
Sabonis (SAC) hands off the ball in Reaves' (LAL) path and is firming up when contact occurs.
Westbrook (LAL) places his arm against Barnes' (SAC) right arm and initiates contact that affects his driving shot attempt.
Sabonis (SAC) and Davis (LAL) engage and disengage with one another and marginal contact occurs as the pick is set.
Sabonis (SAC) contests the driving shot attempt and marginal contact occurs with Westbrook's (LAL) arm after the release.
Barnes (SAC) and Davis (LAL) mutually engage and disengage with one another during rebounding.
Westbrook (LAL) lightly brushes Fox's (SAC) side contesting his driving shot attempt.
Huerter (SAC) brings his arm toward Walker IV's (LAL) path and marginal contact occurs during Walker IV's (LAL) drive.
Monk (SAC) contests the jump shot attempt and marginal contact occurs with Beverley's (LAL) arm after the release.
Barnes (SAC) briefly wraps his arm around Davis (LAL) and removes it and Davis and Barnes make incidental foot to foot contact that causes Davis to lose his balance.
Reaves (LAL) briefly places his hand to Huerter's (SAC) side and immediately slides his hand off as Huerter secures the loose ball.
Reaves (LAL) legally contests Fox's (SAC) jump shot attempt.
Sabonis (SAC) and Davis (LAL) engage and disengage with one another and marginal contact occurs prior to the inbound pass.
Barnes (SAC) legally contests Walker IV's (LAL) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Westbrook (LAL) commits a take foul on Barnes (SAC).
Sabonis (SAC) legally contest Davis' (LAL) jump shot attempt and marginal body contact occurs after his release.
Westbrook (LAL) places his hands to Barnes' (SAC) backside and marginal contact occurs as they pursue the long rebound.
The ball momentarily gets caught on the rim during Reaves' (LAL) jump shot attempt, but quickly rolls off and play should have been allowed to continue.
After the ball becomes loose, Reaves (LAL) and Barnes (SAC) mutually engage and disengage with one another.
Sabonis (SAC) legally contests Reaves's (LAL) jump shot attempt.
